## Unit 3 Day 11-13: HTML and CSS

First, let's explore the sixth lesson in the curriculum. To begin, find your ECS Version 5 curriculum and open to page 114-115.

<a href="http://code.org/ecs#page=114" target="_blank">Access a Digital Copy of the Lesson >></a>


#### Key Concepts

1. Students will explore and apply the concept of separating style from structure by keeping separate html and css files.

2. Students need to know that the name of the style sheet needs to have a .css extension and be saved in the web folder.

#### Common Difficulties

This lesson is intended to further students understanding of separating style from structure by keeping separate html and css files which means you as the teacher needs to know this distinction as well so that you can guide them.

You may need to refer to the resources listed such as [http://www.georgebenainous.com/web](http://www.georgebenainous.com/web)to feel comfortable leading the discussions for this lesson.

